<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Clayton</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-21"><hi rend="italic">June 21,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 727.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to ackowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 1413, of the 11th instant, on the subject of the arrest and
                            imprisonment of Nathaniel F. Bonsall.</p>
                        <p>In reply, I have to inform you that, from the appearance of the case as
                            it is now before the Department, it is not perceived that an}’ further
                            action can be taken.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>